31namespace webrtc {

33namespace {
34
35#if defined(WEBRTC_USE_H264)
36bool g_rtc_use_h264 = true;
37#endif
38
39// If H.264 OpenH264/FFmpeg codec is supported.
40bool IsH264CodecSupported() {
41#if defined(WEBRTC_USE_H264)
42 return g_rtc_use_h264;
43#else
44 return false;
45#endif
46}
47
48} // namespace
49
50SdpVideoFormat CreateH264Format(H264Profile profile,
51 H264Level level,
52 const std::string& packetization_mode) {
53 const absl::optional<std::string> profile_string =
54 H264ProfileLevelIdToString(H264ProfileLevelId(profile, level));
55 RTC_CHECK(profile_string);
56 return SdpVideoFormat(
57 cricket::kH264CodecName,
58 {{cricket::kH264FmtpProfileLevelId, *profile_string},
59 {cricket::kH264FmtpLevelAsymmetryAllowed, "1"},
60 {cricket::kH264FmtpPacketizationMode, packetization_mode}});
61}
62
63void DisableRtcUseH264() {
64#if defined(WEBRTC_USE_H264)
65 g_rtc_use_h264 = false;
66#endif
67}
68
69std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> SupportedH264Codecs() {
70 if (!IsH264CodecSupported())
71 return std::vector<SdpVideoFormat>();
72 // We only support encoding Constrained Baseline Profile (CBP), but the
73 // decoder supports more profiles. We can list all profiles here that are
74 // supported by the decoder and that are also supersets of CBP, i.e. the
75 // decoder for that profile is required to be able to decode CBP. This means
76 // we can encode and send CBP even though we negotiated a potentially
77 // higher profile. See the H264 spec for more information.
78 //
79 // We support both packetization modes 0 (mandatory) and 1 (optional,
80 // preferred).
81 return {CreateH264Format(H264Profile::kProfileBaseline, H264Level::kLevel3_1,
82 "1"),
83 CreateH264Format(H264Profile::kProfileBaseline, H264Level::kLevel3_1,
84 "0"),
85 CreateH264Format(H264Profile::kProfileConstrainedBaseline,
86 H264Level::kLevel3_1, "1"),
87 CreateH264Format(H264Profile::kProfileConstrainedBaseline,
88 H264Level::kLevel3_1, "0")};
89}
90
91std::unique_ptr<H264Encoder> H264Encoder::Create(
92 const cricket::VideoCodec& codec) {
93 RTC_DCHECK(H264Encoder::IsSupported());
94#if defined(WEBRTC_USE_H264)
95 RTC_CHECK(g_rtc_use_h264);
96 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Creating H264EncoderImpl.";
97 return std::make_unique<H264EncoderImpl>(codec);
98#else
99 RTC_NOTREACHED();
100 return nullptr;
101#endif
102}
103
104bool H264Encoder::IsSupported() {
105 return IsH264CodecSupported();
106}
107
108std::unique_ptr<H264Decoder> H264Decoder::Create() {
109 RTC_DCHECK(H264Decoder::IsSupported());
110#if defined(WEBRTC_USE_H264) && !defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
111 RTC_CHECK(g_rtc_use_h264);
112 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Creating H264DecoderImpl.";
113 return std::make_unique<H264DecoderImpl>();
114#else
115 RTC_NOTREACHED();
116 return nullptr;
117#endif
118}
119
120bool H264Decoder::IsSupported() {
121 return IsH264CodecSupported();
122}
